Why this is a problem
XPath injection allows attackers to alter the structure of XML queries, which can lead to unauthorized data access or security bypasses. Preventing this protects the integrity and confidentiality of XML data processing.

How to fix it
Use LINQ to XML instead of XPath queries, and avoid passing unsanitized user input directly into XPath functions such as XPathEvaluate, XPathSelectElement, and XPathSelectElements. When using LINQ to XML, ensure that user input is safely handled and not concatenated directly into queries.

